The paper focuses on software security and optimization, which suggests it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper presents a debloating framework built on a compiler toolchain, which could fall under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The use of compiler toolchain also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of debloating on program functionality, which could fall under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents results of experiments and optimizations, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
